											 New Types of Azure Virtual Machines 					
					 
						 Posted on   September 22, 2014 						 by   Glenn Berry   					 

					 
						 Microsoft has announced a new set of VM sizes for Azure Virtual Machines , known as the D-series, that have faster vCPUs (compared to their older A-series Azure VMs) and local, temporary SSDs. 
 These local SSDs are touted as being good locations to use the new Buffer Pool Extensions (BPE) feature that was added to SQL Server 2014, for both Standard Edition and Enterprise Edition. 